Steps.Message: Update at 17:10 - Hi, it's Amy from the text messaging team. We've liaised with our engineers and they have advised that they are in the process of making final repairs to the secondary fault. Within the next hour, the team will need to turn off some power in the area again in order to disconnect a temporary generator from the network. We are anticipating that the power will be off for approximately 15 minutes whilst the team remove the generator and connect you back onto the main electricity supply. We are not expecting all the power to go off in the area due to the nature of the fault. We're sorry for the disruption that this has caused you.

We became aware of this power cut at 17:52. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing

Steps.Message: All power in the area should be back on. We’re really sorry for any disruption this caused.
Steps.Name: Power restored
